commit_message:
Add backrefs to api db models

Some api database models did not have backrefs setup for their
relationships which affected how queries were done and the result sets
were handled. This diverged from how it's done elsewhere in Nova which
led to many questions on reviews. So backrefs have been added to bring
this in line with the rest of the models.

back_populates is used in one spot which is functionally equivalent to
backref except that it requires the relationship to be defined on both
sides. Since one side was already defined I used back_populate here to
minimize changes.

Change-Id: If653143738c91771e845ceb127e60cead8d40fae

commit_message:
EMC VMAX - Limit SG and MV to 64 characters

VMAX restricts storage group and masking view names to a maximum
length of 64 characters. This patch only adds extra unit tests to
prove that both MV and SG names are below the 64 chars in all
scenarios.

Change-Id: I72917a56083eb25f876b9cdeaa30511793922497

subject: Use any media repository if it exists
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-03-22 13:58:53.000000000', 'files': ['requirements.txt', 'nova_powervm/virt/powervm/__init__.py', 'nova_powervm/virt/powervm/media.py', 'nova_powervm/tests/virt/powervm/test_media.py'], 'message': "Use any media repository if it exists

A VIOS is only allowed to have one virtual media repository on it.
Attempts to create a second one will fail.

The previous logic in ConfigDrivePowerVM would always try to create a
media repository on the volume group specified via the
vopt_media_volume_group conf option (or rootvg if the option was
omitted).  If a media repository already existed on a different volume
group, this would cause a failure.

With this change set, we look for an existing media repository on any
volume group, on any live VIOS, and use the first one we find.  Only if
we don't find one do we attempt to create it on the configured
vopt_media_volume_group / rootvg.

Change-Id: If9770c2a62a7f7362b198df4b8c4c72acf3e75a6
Closes-Bug: 1558253
"}]
commit_message:
Use any media repository if it exists

A VIOS is only allowed to have one virtual media repository on it.
Attempts to create a second one will fail.

The previous logic in ConfigDrivePowerVM would always try to create a
media repository on the volume group specified via the
vopt_media_volume_group conf option (or rootvg if the option was
omitted).  If a media repository already existed on a different volume
group, this would cause a failure.

With this change set, we look for an existing media repository on any
volume group, on any live VIOS, and use the first one we find.  Only if
we don't find one do we attempt to create it on the configured
vopt_media_volume_group / rootvg.

Change-Id: If9770c2a62a7f7362b198df4b8c4c72acf3e75a6
Closes-Bug: 1558253

commit_message:
Remove all interface configs for simple-init

We are currently removing only eth0 network config in the simple-init
element (since simple-init is responsible for networking if you are
using it). We install an eth1 as well in elements such as debootstrap.
Lets just rm eth*.

Change-Id: Id9ea8c5e402f3a06b9064a939ad4b2e168cd6223

commit_message:
Update devstack plugin for dependent packages

Recent changes to the gate base images [1] removed a package
neutron-lbaas requires (software-properties-common).
This patch loads it before running 'add-apt-repository'.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/292573

This is not a cherry-pick from master as there were issues
getting "System Packages" to work correctly in the gate
in stable/liberty.

Change-Id: Id16da90e195ede8a7565b3265374cb603b6eb898
Closes-Bug: #1558289

subject: Restores SIGPIPE on script processes
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-03-22 14:18:31.000000000', 'files': ['muranoagent/executors/application/__init__.py'], 'message': "Restores SIGPIPE on script processes

There is an issue https://bugs.python.org/issue1652
in Python 2.7 which was resolved in Py3.

By default Python sets SIGPIPE to SIG_IGN on startup, because
it prefers to check every write and raise an IOError exception rather
than taking SIGPIPE. This is all well and good for Python itself.
However, non-Python Unix subprocesses generally expect to have

commit_message:
Restores SIGPIPE on script processes

There is an issue https://bugs.python.org/issue1652
in Python 2.7 which was resolved in Py3.

By default Python sets SIGPIPE to SIG_IGN on startup, because
it prefers to check every write and raise an IOError exception rather
than taking SIGPIPE. This is all well and good for Python itself.
However, non-Python Unix subprocesses generally expect to have
SIGPIPE set to the default action, since that's what will happen if
they're started from a normal shell.

As a result scripts with piping that is terminated in reverse chain
order are never exit.

See more info here:
http://www.enricozini.org/blog/2009/debian/python-pipes/

Closes-Bug: #1524347
Change-Id: Ia015e7fd46912f6a0be97a6b9c297f8d14fd3f7c

commit_message:
Cleanup threads config option

Allow the user to change the number of cleanup threads via the rally
config. When scaling out to thousands of instances, the cleanup can take
forever with the static 20 threads.

Change-Id: I0fa5c6ba2dec01b6a33a336e635713602ce9a61c

commit_message:

I missed a step in the transition to oslo.log, which appears to be
causing Liberty CI jobs to fail.  This change properly handles
oslo.log conf options as described in [1].

Also removes openstack-common.conf as it is no longer used.

revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2016-02-23 07:44:38.000000000', 'files': ['specs/newton/list-manage-existing.rst'], 'message': 'List volumes/snapshots for manage-existing

Cinder currently has the ability to take over the management of existing
volumes and snapshots ("manage existing") and to relinquish management of
volumes and snapshots ("unmanage"). The API to manage an existing volume takes
a reference, which is a driver-specific string that is used to identify the
volume on the storage backend. This process is currently confusing and error
prone. This spec's purpose is to detail APIs for listing volumes and snapshots
available for management to make this flow more user-friendly. Allowing the
listing of available volumes/snapshots will allow for the creation of an
easy-to-use GUI to migrate existing volumes to a new OpenStack environment, or
to recover in the case the Cinder database is lost.

blueprint: list-manage-existing
Change-Id: Ie2a22deaac61ffe3ca69f62012d4cf894638c83c
'}]
commit_message:
List volumes/snapshots for manage-existing

Cinder currently has the ability to take over the management of existing
volumes and snapshots ("manage existing") and to relinquish management of
volumes and snapshots ("unmanage"). The API to manage an existing volume takes
a reference, which is a driver-specific string that is used to identify the
volume on the storage backend. This process is currently confusing and error
prone. This spec's purpose is to detail APIs for listing volumes and snapshots
available for management to make this flow more user-friendly. Allowing the
listing of available volumes/snapshots will allow for the creation of an
easy-to-use GUI to migrate existing volumes to a new OpenStack environment, or
to recover in the case the Cinder database is lost.

blueprint: list-manage-existing
Change-Id: Ie2a22deaac61ffe3ca69f62012d4cf894638c83c

[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-03-22 13:50:55.000000000', 'files': ['muranoagent/executors/application/__init__.py'], 'message': "Restores SIGPIPE on script processes

There is an issue https://bugs.python.org/issue1652
in Python 2.7 which was resolved in Py3.

By default Python sets SIGPIPE to SIG_IGN on startup, because
it prefers to check every write and raise an IOError exception rather
than taking SIGPIPE. This is all well and good for Python itself.
However, non-Python Unix subprocesses generally expect to have
SIGPIPE set to the default action, since that's what will happen if
they're started from a normal shell.

As a result scripts with piping that is terminated in reverse chain
order are never exit.

See more info here:
http://www.enricozini.org/blog/2009/debian/python-pipes/

Closes-Bug: #1524347
Change-Id: Ia015e7fd46912f6a0be97a6b9c297f8d14fd3f7c
"}]
commit_message:
Restores SIGPIPE on script processes

There is an issue https://bugs.python.org/issue1652
in Python 2.7 which was resolved in Py3.

By default Python sets SIGPIPE to SIG_IGN on startup, because
it prefers to check every write and raise an IOError exception rather
than taking SIGPIPE. This is all well and good for Python itself.
However, non-Python Unix subprocesses generally expect to have
SIGPIPE set to the default action, since that's what will happen if
they're started from a normal shell.

As a result scripts with piping that is terminated in reverse chain
order are never exit.

See more info here:
http://www.enricozini.org/blog/2009/debian/python-pipes/

Closes-Bug: #1524347
Change-Id: Ia015e7fd46912f6a0be97a6b9c297f8d14fd3f7c

commit_message:
Bootable filter for listening volumes from CLI

Currently cinder treats all values passed to it as True
for bootable filter in volume GET call.

For ex, if bootable=invalid, it converts it into True being
bootable as boolean value in db table 'volume'.

Need to update filtering functionality in cinder to address
'True' and 'False' values seperately.

Existing behavior will be kept same.
Only True/False/true/false input handling is done to treat
true/false seperately
(In current behavior, whatever input is passed for boolean
parameter, cinder convetrs it to True)

Implements : blueprint select-volume-through-bootable-option

Closes-Bug: #1535749

Change-Id: I1f1ec20441b28e01bf07bc4f60d848b653e58d58

commit_message:
Remove the database creation & messaging tasks from the role

This change removes the database creation and messaging tasks
from this role as the role should expect to be given a database
and message queue.

The test plays have been updated to do the messaging/db tasks
appropriately.

Change-Id: I8e3603faff2de90c4794cd28c57e55aca6665741

[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-03-21 23:12:14.000000000', 'files': ['monasca_common/kafka/consumer.py'], 'message': "Partition rebalance broken in kafka-python 0.9.5

Our partiton rebalance mechanism broke on the upgrade from kafka-python 0.9.2
to 0.9.5.  Rather than fiddling with the internals of the kafka consumer object
we're now reconstructing the consumer object after each rebalance and handing
it the specific partitions it needs to worry about.

Closes-bug: #1560178
Change-Id: I469ceb28538db1f36918f211eaea4fcfdaa17649
"}]
commit_message:
Partition rebalance broken in kafka-python 0.9.5

Our partiton rebalance mechanism broke on the upgrade from kafka-python 0.9.2
to 0.9.5.  Rather than fiddling with the internals of the kafka consumer object
we're now reconstructing the consumer object after each rebalance and handing
it the specific partitions it needs to worry about.

Closes-bug: #1560178
Change-Id: I469ceb28538db1f36918f211eaea4fcfdaa17649

commit_message:
Pin cryptography library to <1.2

cryptography and pyOpenSSL aren't playing well together
right now, pin to a known good version until the fixes
merge since Lbaas is blocking all neutron stable/liberty
changes.

See these for reference:

https://github.com/pyca/pyopenssl/pull/418
https://botbot.me/freenode/cryptography-dev/2016-03-18/?msg=62470517&page=2

We can undo this once a fixed version is pushed.

Change-Id: I2007a9a2cfb3ecac0e48a3577d87a22eeffb275d
Partial-bug: #1558289

commit_message:
Multipath fixes for problems of real hardware

Sometimes udevadm is not triggered after creating
parition for multipath devices. So we need to trigger
it manually, but this procedure creates bad links.
Like serial1 instead of serial-part1. To remove them
we need to refresh all links for dev mapper, before
calling pvcreate.

Change-Id: Ic4411f02ede819d3bc052377371f0628b2865050
Closes-Bug: #1555664

Use assert_called_once_with() instead of assert_called_with()

If one API is only called once, we'd better use assert_called_once_with()
to check the call.

commit_message:
Add precommit to the driver create/update_bgpvpn API

With precommits, bgpvpn drivers will be able to block any change
that a REST request wants to apply to the DB with create/update_bgpvpn.

If the driver raises an exception during its precommit method,
the REST client will have a HTTP 500 error, and nothing will be
commited in the DB.

Change-Id: I1f0e5d4a555fe0802ecc873f7ae0f2ac121fc783
Closes-bug: 1557608

commit_message:
Switch from MySQL-python to PyMySQL

As part of the cross-project effort [1] to prepare OpenStack for
Python3 as the primary Python version used, the decision has been
made to switch from using MySQL-python to PyMySQL [2].

This patch switches Ironic to use the PyMySQL library.

[1] https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/liberty-cross-project-python3
[2] https://review.openstack.org/184388

Change-Id: I9c6906c37213a2a48c9aab3988b392fb7397ea90

commit_message:
Support Allowed address pairs

This patch adds the necessary code to support the allowed
address pairs extension.

This patch also stores the ip address and mac address of the
allowed address pairs configured on a port  into the
OVN NB Logical_Port.port_security so that ovn-northd can add
the necessary port security logical flows.

Change-Id: I3a604328cd3d816e8288904d69aa06fdf6f57749
Closes-bug: #1469261

subject: Re-deploy the venv if it mismatches the repo
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-03-22 14:44:00.000000000', 'files': ['tasks/ironic_install.yml', 'defaults/main.yml'], 'message': 'Re-deploy the venv if it mismatches the repo

We currently have two issues with venvs:

- if you update your venv on the repo server, it is not possible for
  that updated venv to land on the service's container as the get_url
  task always skips if the file exists (even if the file is different)
- if you have an updated venv on the repo server and forcefully delete
  the cached venv tarball on the service's container, the new tarball
  will get unarchived over top of the existing venv

This commit does the following:

- gets the checksum of the /var/cache tarball and downloads checksum
  file from repo server
- updates "Attempt venv download" to only download the venv if the
  cache doesn't exist or if the local and remote checksums differ
- adds a "force: true" to "Attempt venv download" task so that the venv
  tarball will get re-downloaded when the when condition is true (this
  is necessary otherwise the download will get skipped since the
  destination already exists)
- adds a new task "Remove existing venv" so we can first remove the
  venv before we unarchive the potentially new venv from the repo
  server
- updates "Create neutron venv dir" and "Unarchive pre-built venv"
  tasks to only proceed if "neutron_get_venv | changed", which
  prevents these tasks from running when they the venv tarball hasn't
  changed
- adds multiple service restarts to
  os_neutron/tasks/neutron_install.yml so that neutron will restart
  correctly should the venv/packages update without any associated
  config changes

NOTE: The reason why we compare local and remote checksum is to avoid
      unnecessarily downloading the venv when the checksums are in fact
      the same.  On small deploys this is more or less a non-issue but
      if a deploy w/ thousands of compute nodes re-runs playbooks we
      want to limit the venv downloads when it's unnecessary.

Change-Id: Ie0ba2956e5bf90cec6615171b50a2397c7624257
'}]
commit_message:
Re-deploy the venv if it mismatches the repo

We currently have two issues with venvs:

- if you update your venv on the repo server, it is not possible for
  that updated venv to land on the service's container as the get_url
  task always skips if the file exists (even if the file is different)
- if you have an updated venv on the repo server and forcefully delete
  the cached venv tarball on the service's container, the new tarball
  will get unarchived over top of the existing venv

This commit does the following:

- gets the checksum of the /var/cache tarball and downloads checksum
  file from repo server
- updates "Attempt venv download" to only download the venv if the
  cache doesn't exist or if the local and remote checksums differ
- adds a "force: true" to "Attempt venv download" task so that the venv
  tarball will get re-downloaded when the when condition is true (this
  is necessary otherwise the download will get skipped since the
  destination already exists)
- adds a new task "Remove existing venv" so we can first remove the
  venv before we unarchive the potentially new venv from the repo
  server
- updates "Create neutron venv dir" and "Unarchive pre-built venv"
  tasks to only proceed if "neutron_get_venv | changed", which
  prevents these tasks from running when they the venv tarball hasn't
  changed
- adds multiple service restarts to
  os_neutron/tasks/neutron_install.yml so that neutron will restart
  correctly should the venv/packages update without any associated
  config changes

NOTE: The reason why we compare local and remote checksum is to avoid
      unnecessarily downloading the venv when the checksums are in fact
      the same.  On small deploys this is more or less a non-issue but
      if a deploy w/ thousands of compute nodes re-runs playbooks we
      want to limit the venv downloads when it's unnecessary.

Change-Id: Ie0ba2956e5bf90cec6615171b50a2397c7624257

commit_message:
Consolidate pip install tasks

The pip install tasks were distributed into many files with no clear
benefit from doing so. This patch consolidates the pip install tasks
to ensure that they are all handled together, are all installed into
the appropriate venv, and all use the right constraints.

Change-Id: I8bad68c57c0ffa986817aa80d79e9d2ab4b86a3d

commit_message:
Create multipath disk devices with libvirt driver

- add environment variable SLAVE_MULTIPATH_DISKS_COUNT:
  * default = 0 : multipath disabled
  * if 1 or more: add specified amount of disk devices that
    have the same volume file and the same serial.
    bus set to 'scsi'.
  SLAVE_MULTIPATH_DISKS_COUNT is applied only to slave nodes,
  on 'system' and 'cinder' disks. 'swift' remains on 'virtio'.
- add WWN to disk devices in node XML, if the same volume is
  attached to more than one disk device.
- added unit test for a node with attached multipath devices.
- move class DiskDevice from models/network to models/volume
- re-order keys in the template 'default.yaml' for more suitable
  reading.

Change-Id: I9762dd17b72c404690c8601eca90ec7b82794d2a
blueprint: fuel-devops-multipath-disk-devices

commit_message:
3PAR use same LUN id for each export path

When multipath is enabled, and the 3PAR driver is configured
to export a VLUN over N iSCSI IP(ports), we now use the same
LUN ID for each iSCSI IP export.  Previously, when we would
export a volume over N iSCSI ports, we would get a new LUN ID
for each iSCSI port.

Change-Id: Ide0ce373a14f348a554688dee9b699feed3c5f26
Closes-Bug: #1551994

commit_message:
Support port security API extension

This patch adds the necessary code to support the port security
extension. The user can enable or disable port security for each
port.

This patch also stores the ip addresses of a port into the
OVN NB Logical_Port.port_security so that ovn-northd can add
the necessary port security logical flows.

Change-Id: Ic7932feffb10562fef35a63d8fa02f5f8fc94c4c
Closes-bug: #1496595

commit_message:
Refactored 'save_only' mode

 * Use common logic for 'normal' and 'save_only' modes -
   call modules logic in both cases
 * Remove hardcoded default settings
 * Fix 'save' for situation w/o parent section in config
 * Avoid code duplication in 'save' methods
 * (Minor) Fixed imports order in modules

Change-Id: Id54f1229915336b8aebdb36562e06e2596c003f1
Closes-Bug: #1502110
Depends-On: Ib696846892fa3661c25d7e779392688c1240c553

commit_message:
Move to Fedora 23 for Libvirt/LXC Nova Test

So far, Fedora 23 have seemed to be the most
stable in local simulations. This patch will
allow us to test that case using upstream
infrastructure.

Related-Bug: 1552740
Partial-Bug: 1558268

Change-Id: Ib77549e99b1e7f87062455af7ea6fd70c8650f17

commit_message:
Enable developer mode with upper-constraints

This commit adds the ability to install Ironic without requiring an
OpenStack-Ansible pip wheel repository.

In 'developer mode' the git source is cloned directly and the services
are installed directly from the git clone with its requirements being
installed from pypi. The OpenStack upper-constraints file is also used
to ensure that the install is executed using the appropriately tested
set of pypi packages.

commit_message:
Fix $PROJECTS variable for tempest-dsvm-nova-os-vif job

Latest change (Ifa4bc72b35e4d152faca8edbae9356854d7a71ce) for
tempest-dsvm-nova-os-vif job changed the way to trigger devstack
to install os-vif. But these changes also require adding the project to
the $PROJECTS variable in the job definition.
This patch adds missing changes in $PROJECTS variable.

Change-Id: Idaf5c3698edc09a110002f99c41e8b828b313536

subject: Ensure namedpipe IO workers clean up handles when stopping
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-03-21 17:09:27.000000000', 'files': ['os_win/tests/utils/io/test_namedpipe.py', 'os_win/utils/io/namedpipe.py'], 'message': 'Ensure namedpipe IO workers clean up handles when stopping

At the moment, when an exception is encountered by the namedpipe
IO workers (for example, the named pipe is closed), they are
stopped but the file handles remain open until the namedpipe
handler is explicitly stopped.

This patch changes this, ensuring that when a named pipe IO worker
ends its execution, it gracefully closes the file handles.

Change-Id: If696b082fee719c6d3bb50888f87c1f0aeea5331
'}]
commit_message:
Ensure namedpipe IO workers clean up handles when stopping

At the moment, when an exception is encountered by the namedpipe
IO workers (for example, the named pipe is closed), they are
stopped but the file handles remain open until the namedpipe
handler is explicitly stopped.

This patch changes this, ensuring that when a named pipe IO worker
ends its execution, it gracefully closes the file handles.

Change-Id: If696b082fee719c6d3bb50888f87c1f0aeea5331

net-bgpvpn: control gate settings from rc scripts

This change updates jenkins job definitions for
networking-bgpvpn so that gate settings can be controlled
from rcfiles in the networking-bgpvpn repo, instead
of being hardcoded.

This change removes a few lines because they now
are present in the rcfile that this change enables.

subject: Run extra specs through TaskManager and use requests
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-03-21 14:04:03.000000000', 'files': ['shade/tests/unit/test_caching.py', 'shade/tests/unit/test_meta.py', 'shade/tests/unit/test_shade.py', 'shade/meta.py', 'shade/task_manager.py', 'shade/tests/fakes.py', 'shade/tests/unit/test_flavors.py', 'shade/_tasks.py', 'shade/openstackcloud.py'], 'message': "Run extra specs through TaskManager and use requests

The previous fix for flavors and extra_specs made API calls that did not
get wrapped in the TaskManager. This is really novaclient's fault for
having a weird interface. Change it to call in through the api.client
interface on the flavor manager in novaclient so we can Task it.

Some clouds return the extra_specs dict in a key called
OS-FLV-WITH-EXT-SPECS:extra_specs. If that's present, just add it to the
return dict instead of making the extra API call.

There are two instances of making raw REST calls to nova via the
client.api property of novaclient. However, we have access to a proper
keystoneauth Session object we can mount properly on the compute
service, so instead of using weird internal novaclient API - let's just
use requests.

In order to support this, we need to do the request_id logic ourselves.
Luckily for us it's easier logic than in python-*client because we don't
have to deal with appending request ids since we're never in the middle
of a request chain.

Change-Id: Ia8e40d542f98f0ccc55131ca277b862cffeecb12
"}]
commit_message:
Run extra specs through TaskManager and use requests

The previous fix for flavors and extra_specs made API calls that did not
get wrapped in the TaskManager. This is really novaclient's fault for
having a weird interface. Change it to call in through the api.client
interface on the flavor manager in novaclient so we can Task it.

Some clouds return the extra_specs dict in a key called
OS-FLV-WITH-EXT-SPECS:extra_specs. If that's present, just add it to the
return dict instead of making the extra API call.

There are two instances of making raw REST calls to nova via the
client.api property of novaclient. However, we have access to a proper
keystoneauth Session object we can mount properly on the compute
service, so instead of using weird internal novaclient API - let's just
use requests.

In order to support this, we need to do the request_id logic ourselves.
Luckily for us it's easier logic than in python-*client because we don't
have to deal with appending request ids since we're never in the middle
of a request chain.

Change-Id: Ia8e40d542f98f0ccc55131ca277b862cffeecb12

[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-03-19 18:29:06.000000000', 'files': ['shade/tests/unit/test_caching.py', 'shade/_utils.py', 'shade/operatorcloud.py', 'shade/tests/unit/test_shade.py', 'shade/task_manager.py', 'shade/tests/fakes.py', 'releasenotes/notes/flavor_fix-a53c6b326dc34a2c.yaml', 'shade/tests/functional/test_flavor.py', 'shade/tests/unit/test_flavors.py', 'shade/openstackcloud.py'], 'message': "Bug fix: Make set/unset of flavor specs work again

The 1.2.0 release broke the API methods to set and unset
flavor extra specs because we need the raw object, as returned
from the nova client, to make method calls to change those
values. As a result, a new 'raw' parameter was added to the
submitTask() method of TaskManager to allow us to get these
raw objects back.

Additionally, we were never displaying the 'extra_specs' for
a flavor. This, too, requires a raw object method call.

Flavors are now normalized to remove client cruft and make sure
that 'extra_specs' is always an attribute.

As if that weren't enough, we now do functional tests for these
things! What more could one ask for???

Change-Id: Ie5c132317392cf26df2c8f43e9f07d040119eca0
"}]
commit_message:
Bug fix: Make set/unset of flavor specs work again

The 1.2.0 release broke the API methods to set and unset
flavor extra specs because we need the raw object, as returned
from the nova client, to make method calls to change those
values. As a result, a new 'raw' parameter was added to the
submitTask() method of TaskManager to allow us to get these
raw objects back.

Additionally, we were never displaying the 'extra_specs' for
a flavor. This, too, requires a raw object method call.

Flavors are now normalized to remove client cruft and make sure
that 'extra_specs' is always an attribute.

As if that weren't enough, we now do functional tests for these
things! What more could one ask for???

Change-Id: Ie5c132317392cf26df2c8f43e9f07d040119eca0

commit_message:
Updated role using the Multi-Distro framework

* The default apt packages have been moved into a var file
  that is only loaded when the detected OS is matched.
* The Install task file has had the apt specific tasks moved
  into a named install task file.

commit_message:
Convergence: Run workers in threads

Use thread group manager to run the convergence workers in separate
threads. To cancel an update, the thread group will be stopped.

Update the stack_id to group id in ThreadGroupManager since the id could
now be either stack_id or current traversal id.

Change-Id: I1a077b913a1021bd0c1bc87d5791e60076091f9c

commit_message:
[Spec] Improve atomic actions format

This spec proposes improvements related to atomic actions:
  * rename term "atomic actions" into "actions"
  * store actions as list of dicts instead of OrderedDict
  * introduce nested actions saved in "children" container
  * start and end timestamps
  * get rid of duration time (since we have timestamps)

Blueprint: improve-atomic-actions
Change-Id: Ic22c00cf40c36205628dd3bf18b0f09f92fad8c0

commit_message:
Updated role using the Multi-Distro framework

* The default apt packages have been moved into a var file
  that is only loaded when the detected OS is matched.
* The Install task file has had the apt specific tasks moved
  into a named install task file.

commit_message:
Trove external dependency management

Move all dependency tracking to an external class which simplifies the
relationships and allows managing Trove without necessarily using
packages.

This change also cleans up how the client is handled to make
it more configurable and match other modules.

Finally the reference to the deprecated and non-functional
keystone::python class is dropped.

Change-Id: I943685fbeb114dead80b7465b8f5c564a0bc9fe0

commit_message:
Added custom type vs_config and OVS provider for it

vs_config checks and updates the columns in Open_vSwitch table.
Records are updated only when the value differs from the one set
in 'value' parameter.

This will be used by projects like OVN which depends on the
global configs to even boot up

Change-Id: I87f870463147b41a319f1fc6c4225c35d244e3b9

commit_message:
Run online data migrations for nova

Note that this is actually only required when going from mitaka->newton,
but in order to land things very early in newton, we need this to be
run. Since it's valid in mitaka too, we can go ahead and land it there,
and then copy or move it to from-mitaka later.

Change-Id: Ibc02acc60b1023039f2613f8949b95d55169fd30

reviewers: [{'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 2750, 'name': 'Sean Dague', 'email': 'sean@dague.net', 'username': 'sdague'}, {'_account_id': 6854, 'name': 'YAMAMOTO Takashi', 'email': 'yamamoto@midokura.com', 'username': 'yamamoto'}, {'_account_id': 7118, 'name': 'Ian Wienand', 'email': 'iwienand@redhat.com', 'username': 'iwienand'}, {'_account_id': 9009, 'name': 'Red Hat CI', 'email': 'redhatci@redhat.com', 'username': 'redhatci', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}, {'_account_id': 10385, 'name': 'Citrix XenServer CI', 'username': 'citrix_xenserver_ci', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}, {'_account_id': 12487, 'name': 'vigneshvar', 'email': 'vigneshvar.a.s@gmail.com', 'username': 'vigneshvar'}]
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-11-07 21:42:21.000000000', 'files': ['functions-common', 'stack.sh'], 'message': "Reset no_proxy when the node is installed behind a proxy

Date: Fri Nov 07 16:36:00 2014 -0500
Implements: bugfix BUGFIX

Closes-Bug: 1322200

Problem:
=======
When devstack is called by Trove for installation behind a proxy,
the no proxy variables are set by stack.sh. but it doesn't passed
back to Trove. Thereforethe the installation will fail.

Solution:
========
Save the no_proxy variables in localrc.
This fix is based on the fix for 1291111

Change-Id: Ie7058600266f033af0836bdc4de5a56e823f8c07
"}]
commit_message:
Reset no_proxy when the node is installed behind a proxy

Date: Fri Nov 07 16:36:00 2014 -0500
Implements: bugfix BUGFIX

Closes-Bug: 1322200

Problem:
=======
When devstack is called by Trove for installation behind a proxy,
the no proxy variables are set by stack.sh. but it doesn't passed
back to Trove. Thereforethe the installation will fail.

Solution:
========
Save the no_proxy variables in localrc.
This fix is based on the fix for 1291111

Change-Id: Ie7058600266f033af0836bdc4de5a56e823f8c07

revisions:
[{'number': 35, 'created': '2015-03-16 13:14:31.000000000', 'files': ['functions-common', 'stack.sh'], 'message': 'Reset no_proxy when the node is installed behind a proxy

Date: Mon Mar 16 09:15:00 2015 -0500

Problem:
=======
When devstack is installed behind a proxy with proxy variables
http_proxy and https_proxy being exported and without exporting
no_proxy, the installation will fail. The reason is that any REST
request sent to Keystone will be redirected to the proxy server.

Solution:
========
Fix involves appending no_proxy variable with localhost,HOST_IP,
SERVICE_HOST,RABBIT_HOST,CINDER_SERVICE_HOST, GLANCE_SERVICE_HOST,
HEAT_API_CFN_HOST, KEYSTONE_SERVICE_HOST, KEYSTONE_AUTH_HOST,
if they are not included already and then exporting the variable.

Closes-Bug: 1291111

Change-Id: I3cdace056b74fec111d24d222a886716a063d340
'}]
commit_message:
Reset no_proxy when the node is installed behind a proxy

Date: Mon Mar 16 09:15:00 2015 -0500

Problem:
=======
When devstack is installed behind a proxy with proxy variables
http_proxy and https_proxy being exported and without exporting
no_proxy, the installation will fail. The reason is that any REST
request sent to Keystone will be redirected to the proxy server.

Solution:
========
Fix involves appending no_proxy variable with localhost,HOST_IP,
SERVICE_HOST,RABBIT_HOST,CINDER_SERVICE_HOST, GLANCE_SERVICE_HOST,
HEAT_API_CFN_HOST, KEYSTONE_SERVICE_HOST, KEYSTONE_AUTH_HOST,
if they are not included already and then exporting the variable.

Closes-Bug: 1291111

Change-Id: I3cdace056b74fec111d24d222a886716a063d340

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-03-17 12:54:55.000000000', 'files': ['lib/keystone'], 'message': 'keystone faster password checks

keystone indirectly uses the crypt(3) function for password
checking. Most Linux distribution uses the same
function for handling the password hashes
for example the ones in the /etc/shadow.

The crypt has a rounds parameter which related to how many times the functions,
calculates sha-512 hash.

The glibc default is 5000 rounds, but keystone uses 40000 rounds.
A password check with 40000 rounds is around ~30ms CPU time,
with 5001 ~4ms.

keystone needs to call crypt(3) for every token create,
its cpu usage is very visible.

Change-Id: Ia7c359df0d2f846a16b9fb98937f2995e9791010
'}]
commit_message:
keystone faster password checks

keystone indirectly uses the crypt(3) function for password
checking. Most Linux distribution uses the same
function for handling the password hashes
for example the ones in the /etc/shadow.

The crypt has a rounds parameter which related to how many times the functions,
calculates sha-512 hash.

The glibc default is 5000 rounds, but keystone uses 40000 rounds.
A password check with 40000 rounds is around ~30ms CPU time,
with 5001 ~4ms.

keystone needs to call crypt(3) for every token create,
its cpu usage is very visible.

Change-Id: Ia7c359df0d2f846a16b9fb98937f2995e9791010

commit_message:
Add RAW image support for Ceph

To work in ideal circonstances, Ceph needs a RAW image in Glance. This
allows either Nova or Cinder to take advantage of the copy-on-write
cloning functionnality. This commit introduces a generic change_img_format
function that can be used by any component.
The default behavior will now download the cirros image and will convert
it into RAW.

Change-Id: I0d1157829f7131925d2d6918e8bb0f7cebe1e726
Signed-off-by: Sébastien Han <sebastien.han@enovance.com>

commit_message:

processes output to a temp file and monitor for the write.  This
should assure us the new screen is up and ready to receive commands.

commit_message:
Glance Artifact support in devstack

Artifacts service extends Glance's functionality
to store not only the VM images but any other binary
objects accompanied with composite metadata.

To enable with devstack simply add the following
line to your local.conf

    enable_service g-artifacts

When deployed artifacts will be listening on port 9393.

Change-Id: If77a56e05a46fb5a8752fb566dca74df3e086320
Depends-on: Ia20716f3c75299f796879299da317b2e81496088

subject: Enable pipefail
revisions:
[{'number': 10, 'created': '2015-07-17 05:19:59.000000000', 'files': ['lib/nova', 'lib/heat', 'lib/tempest', 'stack.sh'], 'message': 'Enable pipefail

Enable pipefail so we notice when intermediate commands fail.

This includes a couple of work-around for failing cases.

It is probably arguable that

 $ echo "foo" | grep " bar " | ... do something

is a false-positive of pipefail, if "do something" can handle a blank
string.  I think that the benefit of pipefail outweighs it and you can
write the same thing better in other ways.

Note some overalap with [1] which is where we first discovered these
issues.  Keeping this as a separate thing from the keystone v3 changes
though.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/186682

Change-Id: If2daad2f233f80dc274603a3f1dac2260bd00ea6
'}]
commit_message:
Enable pipefail

Enable pipefail so we notice when intermediate commands fail.

This includes a couple of work-around for failing cases.

It is probably arguable that

 $ echo "foo" | grep " bar " | ... do something

is a false-positive of pipefail, if "do something" can handle a blank
string.  I think that the benefit of pipefail outweighs it and you can
write the same thing better in other ways.

Note some overalap with [1] which is where we first discovered these
issues.  Keeping this as a separate thing from the keystone v3 changes
though.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/186682

Change-Id: If2daad2f233f80dc274603a3f1dac2260bd00ea6

commit_message:
Enable Glance metadata catalog feature

Glance’s Metadata Definitions catalog is a common API hosted by the Glance
service for vendors, admins, services, and users to meaningfully define
available key / value pair and tag metadata. The intent is to enable better
metadata collaboration across artifacts, services, and projects for OpenStack
users.

This feature was added in Juno.

See: http://docs.openstack.org/developer/glance/glancemetadefcatalogapi.html

Related to commit https://review.openstack.org/193264
Change-Id: I87a5b560285d4520faa3c58968343f15abfc480f

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-09-24 23:43:34.000000000', 'files': ['exercises/floating_ips.sh'], 'message': 'Change output filed number from "nova floating-ip-create" for IP

The existing floating_ips.sh script fails when run on a freshly
installed devstack with an error similar to the following:

[Call Trace]
./floating_ips.sh:158:die
[ERROR] ./floating_ips.sh:158 Failure adding floating IP 1 to ex-float

It appears that the code expected the IP address in the first field,
whereas "nova floating-ip-create" returns an ID in the first field and
an IP in the second field. The simplest fix seemed to be to have the
field parser choose the correct field based on current nova output.

This patch changes "get_field 1" to "get_field 2" for the two
"nova floating-ip-create" commands.

Change-Id: Ibcbb06fbd761b88a4869fc583d23d96cc9debc81
'}]
commit_message:
Change output filed number from "nova floating-ip-create" for IP

The existing floating_ips.sh script fails when run on a freshly
installed devstack with an error similar to the following:

[Call Trace]
./floating_ips.sh:158:die
[ERROR] ./floating_ips.sh:158 Failure adding floating IP 1 to ex-float

It appears that the code expected the IP address in the first field,
whereas "nova floating-ip-create" returns an ID in the first field and
an IP in the second field. The simplest fix seemed to be to have the
field parser choose the correct field based on current nova output.

This patch changes "get_field 1" to "get_field 2" for the two
"nova floating-ip-create" commands.

Change-Id: Ibcbb06fbd761b88a4869fc583d23d96cc9debc81

commit_message:
Allow installing python-pip from the package

When python-pip is installed by https://bootstrap.pypa.io/get-pip.py
into CentOS7, there is a case in which it does not move.

The python-pip, which is provided from the distributor or the like, it
can be used more stable. By upgrading to the latest version by the
capability provided in itself, it becomes possible to use the latest
version more stably.

Therefore, install_pip.sh is modified so that you can install python-pip
from the package provided by the distribution and so on.

Change-Id: Iae94a205cedbd0ca4030a16244e8dfc1612ee0e3
Closes-Bug: #1501284

commit_message:
Adding memcached install for Horizon

The session size requirements in Horizon have eclipsed the 4K limit
that signed cookies allow. This is especially true when horizon is
paired with keystone v3. This change is to make sure memcached is
available as a session store for horizon.

Change-Id: I1263a7f7e74c78d27dede65d6b4db74e4567cdde

commit_message:
Grant nova service user only service role

The 'admin' role gives the 'nova' user authority to perform all
sorts of operations on keystone that the 'nova' user doesn't need
to do. The 'nova' user should have only the 'service' role.

This is for security hardening

Change-Id: I32765604fb61e3c2a9cf53fcd6a293ab1a1131a0
Closes-Bug: #1445199

commit_message:
neutron-legacy: Add an explicit knob to enable instance metadata

If Q_METADATA_ENABLED is set to True, configure nova metadata proxy
even if q-meta is disabled.  This allows Neutron backends provide
their alternative implementations.

Here's an example of such an implementation:
https://github.com/midonet/midonet/blob/master/docs/openstack-metadata.md

Change-Id: I32cbae1eb6b642b8106e24d9e76ba87b11b24cbe

commit_message:
Add openstack-libery repo to rdo-release-liberty

Modify stack.sh environment 2 variable which set in
[[epel-bootstrap]] RHEL_RDO_REPO_RPM and RHEL_RDO_REPO_ID

commit_message:
Support user images

When deploy ironic in the baremetal system, we need provide user kernel,
ramdisk and images. This patch add support to this, so that when
IRNOC_HARDWARE is true, these user disks will be uploaded to glance.

Change-Id: I69452b86f1f4eec4cb169923f978cc1bd1ac45b3

commit_message:
Adds neutron linuxbridge-agent support to ironic deployment.

When the Neutron Agent is set to 'linuxbridge', instead of the default
'openvswitch', the baremetal nodes created in libvirt will use bridge
 networking instead of an openvswitch virtualport.

Change-Id: I4bce73368aca8e3954bd7088ddd46b319c6458cd
Closes-Bug: #1327046

Closes-Bug: 1291111
Closes-Bug: 1322200

Problem:
=======
When devstack is installed behind a proxy with proxy variables
http_proxy and https_proxy being exported and without exporting
no_proxy, the installation will fail. The reason is that any REST
request sent to Keystone will be redirected to the proxy server.

Solution:
========
Fix involves appending no_proxy variable with localhost,HOST_IP,
SERVICE_HOST if they are not included already and then exporting
the variable.

'}]
commit_message:
Reset no_proxy when the node is installed behind a proxy

Closes-Bug: 1291111
Closes-Bug: 1322200

Problem:
=======
When devstack is installed behind a proxy with proxy variables
http_proxy and https_proxy being exported and without exporting
no_proxy, the installation will fail. The reason is that any REST
request sent to Keystone will be redirected to the proxy server.

Solution:
========
Fix involves appending no_proxy variable with localhost,HOST_IP,
SERVICE_HOST if they are not included already and then exporting
the variable.

Change-Id: If65cb282adc6f5e4c4507b1422885d81de3da4e8

subject: Start ir-api after ir-cond
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-10-16 13:05:34.000000000', 'files': ['lib/ironic'], 'message': "Start ir-api after ir-cond

In spirit of the work toward rolling upgrades in Ironic, we plan to
begin remoting database calls from the API to the conductor.

In devstack, nova-compute starts before the Ironic processes and begins
polling the API service for resources. If the API service directs DB
calls to the conductor, there is a small window in which the API is up
before the conductor is up, and the API will send a bunch of calls over
the message queue that won't get replies.

Start the conductor service before the API service, so that it's ready
and waiting for calls from the API.

Change-Id: I8a0d92f5b158418f391bc9a0c37f116b529bc967
"}]
commit_message:
Start ir-api after ir-cond

In spirit of the work toward rolling upgrades in Ironic, we plan to
begin remoting database calls from the API to the conductor.

In devstack, nova-compute starts before the Ironic processes and begins
polling the API service for resources. If the API service directs DB
calls to the conductor, there is a small window in which the API is up
before the conductor is up, and the API will send a bunch of calls over
the message queue that won't get replies.

Start the conductor service before the API service, so that it's ready
and waiting for calls from the API.

Change-Id: I8a0d92f5b158418f391bc9a0c37f116b529bc967

commit_message:
Add support for dib based agent ramdisk in lib/ironic

This commit adds support for building and configuring
dib based agent ramdisk for Ironic. The environment
variable IRONIC_IPA_RAMDISK_DISTRO
can be used to mention the preferred distro to build the
ramdisk.

By default, lib/ironic will continue building coreos
based IPA ramdisk. "fedora" and "ubuntu" are supported
values for IRONIC_IPA_RAMDISK_DISTRO.

Change-Id: I55ab7be6fc1f9ba7dc41e53d7d8fc3e951aaf8d4
Closes-Bug: 1510797

commit_message:
Fix keystone configuration for 'tls-proxy' service

Set 'public_endpoint' and 'admin_endpoint' keystone configuration
parameters to use 'https' after enabling 'tls-proxy' service.
If these parameters are not set after enabling 'tls-proxy' service,
then default value is getting used which is http://server:5000.
This needs to be https://server:5000 after enabling 'tls-proxy'.

Change-Id: If6fd02351b1a8be925cc5bb3f28339e2a6f54cd1
Closes-Bug: #1482574

commit_message:
EPEL has not been released for ppc64le until RHEL7.2

EPEL has not been built yet for the ppc64le architecture.  It should
exist for the release of RHEL 7.2.  Therefore do not install it here.
Rather rely on it already being installed for the instances where a
private repository exists.

Change-Id: I834f20e9ceae151788cec3649385da1274d7ba46

commit_message:
Enable ssh validation for Neutron

The 'run_validation' flag is 'False' by default and because of that
some tests that require ssh validation are skipped.
This patch sets the flag to 'True' if Neutron is enabled (and Ironic is
disabled).

Related-Bug: #1507926
Change-Id: I97e7be15855193427146efe0acd03ca0939214c1

subject: WIP: Just a test
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-01-08 05:42:36.000000000', 'files': ['functions-common'], 'message': "WIP: Just a test

Fix SIGITIN hang with apt-get

Fix an issue where apt-get consistently hangs due to a SIGTTIN being
received. This occurs on a 'vanilla' devstack-gate VM, when running an
ironic-grenade job.

Upstream has a bug related to this:
https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=555632

http://www.gnu.org/software/libc/manual/html_node/Job-Control-Signals.html
Macro: int SIGTTIN

    A process cannot read from the user's terminal while it is running
    as a background job. When any process in a background job tries to
    read from the terminal, all of the processes in the job are sent a
    SIGTTIN signal. The default action for this signal is to stop the
    process. For more information about how this interacts with the
    terminal driver, see Access to the Terminal.

Change-Id: I769bba2041a75b5c895816f5c22ddde08927bf62
Closes-Bug: #1532080
"}]
commit_message:
WIP: Just a test

Fix SIGITIN hang with apt-get

Fix an issue where apt-get consistently hangs due to a SIGTTIN being
received. This occurs on a 'vanilla' devstack-gate VM, when running an
ironic-grenade job.

Upstream has a bug related to this:
https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=555632

http://www.gnu.org/software/libc/manual/html_node/Job-Control-Signals.html
Macro: int SIGTTIN

    A process cannot read from the user's terminal while it is running
    as a background job. When any process in a background job tries to
    read from the terminal, all of the processes in the job are sent a
    SIGTTIN signal. The default action for this signal is to stop the
    process. For more information about how this interacts with the
    terminal driver, see Access to the Terminal.

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-11-16 04:42:21.000000000', 'files': ['stack.sh'], 'message': 'Don't redeclare DEST|DATA_DIR|SERVICE_DIR in stack.sh

DEST should be configured by stackrc (which should be created after
local config is sourced, ergo picking up any redirection).  Remove the
redeclaration here, and die if it is not already set.

Similar for DATA_DIR

SERVICE_DIR, introduced in I845f6b5dddce5cffa7165ec58517f9ae5d8632a6,
has never been explicitly created; it gets created when there's a
"mkdir -p" for individual components later.  Add a similar check &

'}]
commit_message:
Don't redeclare DEST|DATA_DIR|SERVICE_DIR in stack.sh

DEST should be configured by stackrc (which should be created after
local config is sourced, ergo picking up any redirection).  Remove the
redeclaration here, and die if it is not already set.

Similar for DATA_DIR

SERVICE_DIR, introduced in I845f6b5dddce5cffa7165ec58517f9ae5d8632a6,
has never been explicitly created; it gets created when there's a
"mkdir -p" for individual components later.  Add a similar check &
creation as the other two just for consistency.

Change-Id: I13c80f62389e841ffce5e0dc8a69b685690d68f3

commit_message:
Add subunit output to the timing infrastructure

This commit adds writing a subunit file to the timing infrastructure
in devstack. This means in addition to printing to stdout at the end
of a run, there will be a subunit stream available at the end of the
run which will contain all the individual timing data which can be
used for trend analysis with a subunit2sql db or visualized with
stackviz.

Change-Id: I4591cad7f353e070d21218843bad2f762870df21

commit_message:
Set DATA_DIR and SERVICE_DIR correctly

Set DEST variable after soucing local.conf so that DATA_DIR and
SERVICE_DIR which depends on DEST would be set correctly to
${DEST}/data and ${DEST}/status rather than /opt/stack/data and
/opt/stack/status.

commit_message:
Expose right identity API version and auth type

The generated userrc files, such as accrc/admin/admin, have
fixed v2password OS_AUTH_TYPE, and contains no REGION
environment variable. This patch outputs these information
into userrc files.

In addition, add an script to clear OS_* environment
viariables.

Closes-bug: 1514372
Change-Id: Ie9b484d0b757c5ee2720dcf6070bf89debb58995

commit_message:
download requirements repo a single time

The install_infra command already downloads the requirements_repo, so it
does not make sense to add a command to download it in the stack.sh file
just before invoking install_infra.

Instead of duplicating the work, we can just postpone the installation
of os-testr after installing infra.

Change-Id: Iacf5d192054496bbdb579535bcc378583485145c

commit_message:
Skip pxelinux binary setup in Ironic for ppc arch

Power architecture has its own embeded bootloader, petitboot, and thus
it doesn't require or uses pxelinux.0 as x86 does so we just skip its
setup in that case.
In fact pxelinux.0 doesn't have a version for ppc architecture.

Change-Id: If1a880f298a17ef53c5417243535841d48369e80

commit_message:
Allow l3 agent RPC worker to create HA network

L3 agent RPC worker assumes that ha_network is already created by API
worker on router create. But if API worker is dead after creating router
in DB, l3 agent RPC worker fails to get HA network. Another case is,
if RPC woker tries to get HA network before it is created by API
worker, it will fail. This change allows RPC worker to create HA network
if not created.

Change-Id: I43757b9d2e51ccc7163f250d79209ddc51739af5

reviewers: [{'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 5170, 'name': 'Microsoft Hyper-V CI', 'email': 'hyper-v_ci@microsoft.com', 'username': 'hyper-v-ci', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}, {'_account_id': 7249, 'name': 'Ann Taraday', 'email': 'akamyshnikova@mirantis.com', 'username': 'AKamyshnikova'}, {'_account_id': 7787, 'name': 'Kevin Benton', 'email': 'kevin@benton.pub', 'username': 'blak111'}, {'_account_id': 9681, 'name': 'Ryu CI', 'email': 'ryu-openstack-review@lists.sourceforge.net', 'username': 'neutronryu', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}, {'_account_id': 10386, 'name': 'OpenDaylight CI', 'email': 'odl-openstack@opendaylight.org', 'username': 'odl-jenkins', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}, {'_account_id': 10692, 'name': 'Brocade Vyatta CI', 'email': 'DL-GRP-VYATTA-OSS@Brocade.com', 'username': 'brocade-oss-service', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}, {'_account_id': 12444, 'name': 'John Schwarz', 'email': 'jschwarz@redhat.com', 'username': 'jschwarz'}, {'_account_id': 14208, 'name': 'Cisco CI', 'email': 'ml2.ci@cisco.com', 'username': 'cisco_ml2_ci', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}, {'_account_id': 14323, 'name': 'HP Networking CI', 'email': 'hpnopenstackci@hp.com', 'username': 'hpn'}, {'_account_id': 14571, 'name': 'Intel Experimental CI', 'email': 'openstack-networking-ci@intel.com', 'username': 'intel-networking-ci', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}, {'_account_id': 15752, 'name': 'Intel SR-IOV CI', 'email': 'sriov-ci@intel.com', 'username': 'sriovci', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}]
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-03-21 06:41:14.000000000', 'files': ['neutron/db/l3_hamode_db.py', 'neutron/tests/unit/db/test_l3_hamode_db.py'], 'message': 'Explicitly delete network from L3HARouterNetwork

Delete network from L3HARouterNetwork if no router exists.

While deleting HA network from "networks" table, it deletes
network entry in L3HARouterNetwork as part of CASCADE delete operation.

But with this, we may have failures in below scenario
(with multiple workers)
1) delete_router called on worker1. worker1 finds no HA router and calls
   delete HA network(but HA network not yet deleted from
   L3HARouterNetwork table and "networks" table)
2) woker2 created a new HA router and this router succefully checked
   for network in L3HARouterNetwork(but yet to create ports)
3) worker1 deleted HA network from L3HARouterNetwork(as part of CASCADE
   operation) and "networks" tables
4) worker2 is trying to create HA interfaces and fails

If we explicitly deleted network from L3HARouterNetwork immediately
after the check for deletion(step 1), it will force routers created
after that(i.e step 2) to create new HA network.
And these routers will use this new HA network and avoid failures.

Change-Id: I2c8da4cda96c1132ceccaf524001b362f58fcbe5
'}]
commit_message:
Explicitly delete network from L3HARouterNetwork

Delete network from L3HARouterNetwork if no router exists.

While deleting HA network from "networks" table, it deletes
network entry in L3HARouterNetwork as part of CASCADE delete operation.

But with this, we may have failures in below scenario
(with multiple workers)
1) delete_router called on worker1. worker1 finds no HA router and calls
   delete HA network(but HA network not yet deleted from
   L3HARouterNetwork table and "networks" table)
2) woker2 created a new HA router and this router succefully checked
   for network in L3HARouterNetwork(but yet to create ports)
3) worker1 deleted HA network from L3HARouterNetwork(as part of CASCADE
   operation) and "networks" tables
4) worker2 is trying to create HA interfaces and fails

If we explicitly deleted network from L3HARouterNetwork immediately
after the check for deletion(step 1), it will force routers created
after that(i.e step 2) to create new HA network.
And these routers will use this new HA network and avoid failures.

Change-Id: I2c8da4cda96c1132ceccaf524001b362f58fcbe5

  10.109.0.0/24.

commit_message:
Allow create DB-independed libvirt networks

- use an unique prefix for bridge/interface names:
    fuel212br1:    # bridges of libvirt networks
    fuel212br1-nic:
    fuel212br2:
    fuel212br2-nic:
    fuel212br3:
    fuel212br3-nic:
    ...
    fuel212net1    # a guest's interfaces
    fuel212net2
    fuel212net3
    fuel212net4
    fuel212net5
    , where '212' is a decimal hash of ENV_NAME and DATABASES, so there
    will be a high chance to get an unique prefix for different envs or
    different databases.

    For bridges, LIBVIRT_BR_PREFIX can be specified instead of
    the prefix 'fuelNNNbr'.

    For interfaces, LIBVIRT_IF_PREFIX can be specified instead of
    the prefix 'fuelNNNnet'.

- check if a CIDR is already used in libvirt before creating
  a libvirt network; pick another CIDR if it is used.
  For example, there is already created network 'test_env_admin' with
  CIDR 10.109.0.0/24

  If 'export REUSE_NETWORK_POOLS=False' (default), then for a new
  libvirt network will be created another CIDR than the existing
  10.109.0.0/24.

  If 'export REUSE_NETWORK_POOLS=True' *and* the network'test_env_admin'
  is *stopped*, then a new network can be created using the same CIDR
  10.109.0.0/24 for different devops environment.
  Thus, the same CIDR can be re-used for several environments located
  on the same host, making possible to share the same routed baremeta
  CIDR between different environments, for example.

Change-Id: I7695c5d1a93b5f642543352876e57d209f4db02e
Implements: blueprint fuel-devops-multiple-databases

is to wait till the tgtd process boots completely before running any

process utilises a unix socket for communication with the user and the
_wait_for_iscsi_daemon function asserts the tgtd process status based

changed from /var/run/tgtd.ipc_abstract_namespace to

(cherry-picked from commit fb920f41ed181c7ec74e3367f2735bccce07e574)

commit_message:
determine tgtd ready status through tgtadm

The intention of the iscsi extension _wait_for_iscsi_daemon function
is to wait till the tgtd process boots completely before running any
iscsi commands through the tgtadm command line utility.  The tgtd
process utilises a unix socket for communication with the user and the
_wait_for_iscsi_daemon function asserts the tgtd process status based
on the socket presence.  The socket name/path to use is not specified
by iscsi extension configuration but rather falls-back to a
(system-wide) default value[1].  Since tgtd version 1.0.60, this path
changed from /var/run/tgtd.ipc_abstract_namespace to
/var/run/tgtd/socket[2] and now causes a false-negative while waiting
for the tgtd process to boot[3].

This patch follows implementation suggestion from the bug report[3] to
avoid relying on the socket presence but rather to check the tgtd
status by trying to communicate through the tgtadm tool.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/ironic-python-agent/blob/
5bbb9ded082f2cfde5e8877e9f33294eb93a5fb7/
ironic_python_agent/extensions/iscsi.py#L47 [2]
https://github.com/fujita/tgt/commit/
d1aa4dcfd691c9409dbad5db49ce6754ce9c1b5a
[3] https://bugs.launchpad.net/ironic-python-agent/+bug/1505923

Closes-Bug: #1505923
Partial-Bug: #1551250
Depends-On: I4c19c96d2d5cd8accb9ed8df6241fc9f0c229e0e
Change-Id: If3284e0b441fe6c2da507640c08a4bbefd9dad2b
(cherry-picked from commit fb920f41ed181c7ec74e3367f2735bccce07e574)

commit_message:
Keep row 'data-display' attr up to date after inline editing a cell

Attribute 'data-display' is used to display warning pop-ups about
destructive actions to table rows. Thus if not updated properly after
editing row entity names inline, it will lead to confirm modal message
being outdated.

Change-Id: I4bbedfce60782230cbfbb7262877ce926753aa66
Closes-Bug: #1481850

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-03-21 11:55:48.000000000', 'files': ['nova/virt/libvirt/driver.py', 'nova/tests/unit/virt/libvirt/test_driver.py'], 'message': "Fix conversion of config disks to qcow2 during resize/migration

finish_migration contains some code which converts raw disks to qcow2
when moving from a host which uses raw disks to a host which uses
qcow2 disks. This was erroneously also converted config disks, which
are hard-coded to be raw even when other disks are qcow2.

This has always been broken, but it wasn't previously exposed because
a subsequent bug unconditionally overwrote the qcow2 config disk with
a new, raw one. Change I03e08fae97416ebe5cdedcf238a06d1b90203c5d
changed the order of these 2 events, so that the erroneously-converted
config drive was no longer overwritten, resulting in a qcow2 file
being presented to the instance as raw.

This change explicitly filters out config disks from conversion.

Change-Id: I6bf3cd4f9e0e152bf69732d9a17f93c86dedbd40
Closes-Bug: #1558343
(cherry picked from commit 29fb0aca1623eb0c4a565d728501667a4c5e8136)
"}]
commit_message:
Fix conversion of config disks to qcow2 during resize/migration

finish_migration contains some code which converts raw disks to qcow2
when moving from a host which uses raw disks to a host which uses
qcow2 disks. This was erroneously also converted config disks, which
are hard-coded to be raw even when other disks are qcow2.

This has always been broken, but it wasn't previously exposed because
a subsequent bug unconditionally overwrote the qcow2 config disk with
a new, raw one. Change I03e08fae97416ebe5cdedcf238a06d1b90203c5d
changed the order of these 2 events, so that the erroneously-converted
config drive was no longer overwritten, resulting in a qcow2 file
being presented to the instance as raw.

This change explicitly filters out config disks from conversion.

Change-Id: I6bf3cd4f9e0e152bf69732d9a17f93c86dedbd40
Closes-Bug: #1558343
(cherry picked from commit 29fb0aca1623eb0c4a565d728501667a4c5e8136)

commit_message:
Make node count check a validation

Make the check that runs to verify there are sufficient Ironic nodes a
proper validation. As a validation, it will be affected by the
--validation-errors-nonfatal cli arg, which will allow the deployment to
continue when specified.

This is useful for various testing and devlopment scenarios.

Change-Id: I6acc26d36017577dd0de73458dff24d5cb57024d

The check to make sure there are sufficient hypervisors registered with
enough statistics to handle the deployment is a validation and should be
treated as such.

commit_message:
Fix sysfs service idempotency

Sysfs is kind of "apply params" service, so status should always
return true. Service's resource will prefer the 'status' parameter,
then 'statuscmd' method, then look in the process table.

Partial-Bug: #1524724
Change-Id: I8a13ac4a227195cfb16be89c8fb0a9a9ec3ba1f0

commit_message:
Modify agent: handle multiple port attach sources

This is needed to support, for instance, E-VPN parameters
to be contributed to by the ML2 mech_driver and by the
BGPVPN service plugin.

Other changes in this refactoring:
- Modify BGP VPN port attach handling.
- No need to specify notifiers and vpn types on attach,
  re-sending all plugs for each ports.
- Unplug all notifiers port informations on port detach.

Co-Author: Yannick Thomas <ythomas1.ext@orange.com>
Change-Id: Ifcc2c42c2fcb67762c18aed9bb0b01f0c665967e
(cherry picked from commit c9a03ffbb5946fc5e2ab73047b6a1d142eca102d)

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-03-14 17:28:36.000000000', 'files': ['elements/testenv-worker/os-refresh-config/configure.d/60-setup-testenvs', 'elements/testenv-worker/bin/reset-ovs'], 'message': 'Reset the ovs nightly

Gracefully stop each testenv on a TE host then reset the ovs
config. The purpose here is to work around a ovs bug that is
now more prominent in our testenvs since increasing the number

commit_message:
Import code working with Ironic nodes from os_cloud_config

This patch introduces tripleo_common.utils.{glance,nodes} modules.
The glance one is imported with only import fixes (including importing
a private exceptions module from the glance client).

The nodes.py is a rewritten and fixed version taken from
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/263309/. Main changes:
* Stop hardcoding flavor (e.g. agent, pxe) for each driver
* Support only generic properties with pm_* names. Driver-specific things
  should stay with their prefix. Existing pm_* driver-specific things
  were deprecated.
* Pass through everything that starts with driver-specific prefix to
  node's driver_info.
* Dropped handling Conflict exceptions - ironicclient is doing it for
  some time already (and does better job in it).
* Issue a specific exception for malformed instackenv.json.
* Optimize calls to ironic (use list with details instead of list+get)
* Use 'add' operation instead of 'replace', as it allows both adding
  and overwriting (despite its name).
* Fixed some small issues like adding a dict to a set.

Change-Id: I7efffc5c6627776a20fad4bf4cf266330c4b8b6b

[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-02-22 21:35:42.000000000', 'files': ['test/unit/proxy/controllers/test_obj.py', 'swift/proxy/controllers/obj.py'], 'message': "Set backend content length for fallocate - EC Policy

Currently, the ECObjectController removes the 'content-length' header.
This part is ok, except that value is being used to set
'X-Backend-Obj-Content-Length', so it is always 0.  This leads to not
calling fallocate (details on bug) on a PUT since the size is 0.

This change makes use of some numbers returned from the EC Driver
get_segment_info method in order to calculate the expected on-disk
size that should be allocated.  The EC controller will now set the
'X-Backend-Obj-Content-Length' value appropriately.

Co-Authored-By: Kota Tsuyuzaki

commit_message:
Set backend content length for fallocate - EC Policy

Currently, the ECObjectController removes the 'content-length' header.
This part is ok, except that value is being used to set
'X-Backend-Obj-Content-Length', so it is always 0.  This leads to not
calling fallocate (details on bug) on a PUT since the size is 0.

This change makes use of some numbers returned from the EC Driver
get_segment_info method in order to calculate the expected on-disk
size that should be allocated.  The EC controller will now set the
'X-Backend-Obj-Content-Length' value appropriately.

Co-Authored-By: Kota Tsuyuzaki
Co-Authored-By: John Dickinson
Co-Authored-By: Tim Burke
Change-Id: Ifd16c1438539e6fd9bb2dbcd053d11bea2e09fee
Fixes: bug 1532008

Because of version string of password library ( which is required by

Closes-Bug: 1548591

commit_message:
Devstack failed when install SQLAlchemy-Utils

Devstack failed when install SQLAlchemy-Utils, it will show following
error message.

error in SQLAlchemy-Utils setup command: 'extras_require' must be a
dictionary whose values are strings or lists of strings containing valid
project/version requirement specifiers.

Because of version string of password library ( which is required by
SQLAlchemy-Utils) in extras_require dict is not compatible with
setuptools version above 20.1.1. Maybe we could add setuptools to
upper-constrains before SQLAlchemy-Utils had fixed this issue.

Change-Id: I3b20cff2a7f4fb0f08130dc2a0a588b559cd53af
Closes-Bug: 1548591

commit_message:
Use glance-swift conf for swift backend

For working with Swift backend, Glance needs authentication parameters,
which are supplied to Swift when making calls to its storage system.
Glance will use information from the file specified under parameter
swift_store_config_file. When this parameter is set to the same file
(glance-api.conf), we have lot of non-critical errors in glance-api
log, because of 'Invalid format of swift store config'.
The same problem, when we have RadosGW.

Change-Id: I18ee8f68f7ce793d2580685e79ed636556c57ddd
Related-bug: #1540890

commit_message:
Do not publish translated Debian Guide

The RST Debian Install Guide is not maintained, there's no need to build
and publish it. We continue pushing strings to translate.openstack.org
but will not build it.

commit_message:
New Project - jacket

Now there are many people and enterprises using private clouds
and public clouds, such as OpenStack, VMware vCloud Director, AWS,
Azure and so on. Because clouds' API models are different from
each other, users will meet the following problems:
* High cost of learning
* Large workload to deploy the business in a new cloud
* Difficult to scale out the workload across the different clouds

The target of jacket project is to offer the standard OpenStack
API model for these heterogeneous clouds.

Jacket project's wiki is https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Jacket.

Change-Id: Iaa88e46ec2de1c013611572ed4779e7c289a6e64

commit_message:
Data containers restart and lose data on update/upgrade

During release update/upgrade data container will restart and
will lose data. With pull policy set to missing we never
restart them.

Change-Id: I1b86f0af4481b99f085aa8a59b18003246607444
Closes-Bug: #1521231

commit_message:
Add support of microversion in all compute service clients

Tempest implemented microversion support testing framework
which can set the microversion on service client and further
will be used to pass to API request.

To support setting of microversion on each compute service client
and passing the same in API request, we need to inherit all
compute service clients from BaseComputeClient.

BaseComputeClient class pass the microversion in API request header
and checks the correct microversion is being returned in response.

NOTE- This change to all compute service clients does not change
any interface which means no backward incompatibility is introduced.

After this change, all compute service clients will support to pass
microversion on API request.

commit_message:
Allow cssfiles added by sphinx extensions

Sphinx extensions support the concept of adding css files, which is
often quite important in getting particular theming into
components. The openstackdocstheme currently completely ignores this,
which prevents it being used where sphinx extensions are needed.

Change-Id: Ieb71a071796a37fcfaec2dde9aaa8b153adea27a

commit_message:
Decode injected content when checking length limit

According to the API reference:
http://developer.openstack.org/api-ref-compute-v2.1.html#createServer
the limit of content length should be the limit of decoded
data, not the base64 encoded data.

This patch fix this problem.

Change-Id: I107ff696cd74df494427e4e99b20f9fadb04e364
Closes-bug: #1550671

commit_message:
Prevent update of attrs when new_device_dict is None

Whenver user wants to update VNF and exception is raised in
heat.py, VNF status continues to be PENDING_UPDATE instead of ERROR.
This patch will change VNF status to ERROR whenever update()
in heat.py raises an Exception. This is accomplished by checking
the new_device_dict value before updating attrs in
_update_device_post().

Change-Id: I46b674ba90ced4495dbbb6460bf9981ad8c78bc7
Closes-Bug: #1525808

subject: Drop `delegate_to` and `run_once` in bootstrap task
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-01-22 06:03:16.000000000', 'files': ['ansible/roles/neutron/tasks/deploy.yml', 'ansible/roles/neutron/tasks/bootstrap.yml'], 'message': 'Drop `delegate_to` and `run_once` in bootstrap task

As run_once will always target the first host in the
list, if that host is supposed to skip a set of tasks
(for instance, when), it will also skip any run_once
tasks even though they delegate_to other hosts which
are willing to run that task.

This changes drop delegate_to and run_once, use
`when` replace, Refer to:
http://docs.ansible.com/ansible/playbooks_delegation.html#run-once
https://github.com/ansible/ansible/issues/9784

Change-Id: I82b38ac15e055f193b72b5e5b00c7bb6c7d176e0
Closes-Bug: #1520728
'}]
commit_message:
Drop `delegate_to` and `run_once` in bootstrap task

As run_once will always target the first host in the
list, if that host is supposed to skip a set of tasks
(for instance, when), it will also skip any run_once
tasks even though they delegate_to other hosts which
are willing to run that task.

This changes drop delegate_to and run_once, use
`when` replace, Refer to:
http://docs.ansible.com/ansible/playbooks_delegation.html#run-once
https://github.com/ansible/ansible/issues/9784

Change-Id: I82b38ac15e055f193b72b5e5b00c7bb6c7d176e0
Closes-Bug: #1520728

commit_message:
Avoid cooldown when group size does not change

Cooldown behavior changed in commit:
50cc71e33c40a9e3be604b16f77d3c3cf030a63b

Restore the cooldown behavior so that when a group does not encounter
scaling activity, a cooldown period is not activated.

list of remaining partitions for auditing. If the auditor is restarted, it will
only audit partitions not yet checked. If all partitions on the current device
have been checked, it will simply skip this device. Once all partitions on all

commit_message:
Skip already checked partitions when auditing objects after a restart

The object auditor will save a short status file on each device, containing a
list of remaining partitions for auditing. If the auditor is restarted, it will
only audit partitions not yet checked. If all partitions on the current device
have been checked, it will simply skip this device. Once all partitions on all
disks are successfully audited, all status files are removed.

Closes-Bug: #1183656

Change-Id: Icf1d920d0942ce48f1d3d374ea4d63dbc29ea464

commit_message:
Tintri image direct clone

Fix for the bug 1400966 prevents user from specifying image nfs
share location as location value for an image.
This broke Tintri's image direct clone feature.

This addresses the issue by using provider_location of image
metadata to specify image nfs share location.

DocImpact
Closes-Bug: #1528969
Co-Authored-By: opencompute xuchenx@gmail.com

Change-Id: Icdf2f229d79d5631604e87dd9dd30a1608e6b010

commit_message:
Handling Invalid argument iflag=direct in dd

During volume/snapshot create/delete operations,
dd command is used to clear contents of disk.

Before invoking dd, it is checked if iflag=direct
supports dd or not by executing dd command with
iflag=direct and if=/dev/zero combination.
But this always results in invalid argument
error.

Handling for this argument is done to eliminate
unnecessary call to dd command when it is used
with iflag=direct and if=/dev/zero combination
to check if this argument supports dd or not.

Closes-Bug: #1270362

Change-Id: Ic6dd029ca1a339076e491c38ef3c69315497f189
(cherry picked from commit 5e363eb194e3d33e9a71b7f2f900e5c6dc13a0b1)

commit_message:
Remove gabbi tests that check content-location

The content-location header is an artifact of using httplib2
and not something that ceilometer itself returns. Gabbi is going
to stop using httplib2 (and so is much of OpenStack) so to prepare
for that these tests need to stop testing something that doesn't
really mean anything.

Change-Id: If5aacaf108402146d66fee474793dde1c0a59a7c

commit_message:
Fix sourcemap generation for dev builds

This commit makes gulp unconditionally create external-file sourcemaps
for dev builds. Currently dev builds create both external and inline
sourcemaps, which seems to confuse browsers and often prevents maps
from loading. Additionally, this enables 'loadMaps' for the gulp
sourcemap plugin to make sure that all sourcemaps from browserify are
moved into the external file, fixing maps for dependencies.

Change-Id: I9fcb945d639a60c19c94d688ff26126c8f49e256

commit_message:
Allow option to disable Swift ring management

There are quite a few cases where it is useful to disable ring building on the
nodes. For example:

- using different weights, regions, and zones
- replacing a node in an existing Swift cluster
- adding a new node to an existing cluster
- using storage policies and therefore multiple rings
- using different nodes and disks for account, container and object servers

This patch allows it to disable ring building. Rings need to be maintained
manually then, and copied to all storage and proxy nodes within a cluster.

This patch is similar to I01311ec3ca265b151f8740bf7dc57cdf0cf0df6f, except that
it uses the current templates.

Change-Id: I56978b15823dd6eaf4b6fd3440df2f895e89611a
(cherry picked from commit 83b8bb7bfa420a3f2d03821bf0280f9fb55f1c18)

commit_message:
Add non-voting diskimage-builder jobs

This commit allows the definition of non-voting gate jobs by defining
a new job-suffix. 'extras' was added as a new job pre-suffix because
just 'nv' implies we would be testing the same things as the
non-postfixed variant.  This was done to facilitate adding a Gentoo
non-voting gate job, also in this commit.

Change-Id: I08f35397a4cce05b90d88077922dc38ece5c2b55
Depends-On: I0d2768a912b350e1b2cf40d2fd227fdc767b1bcb

commit_message:
Remove true/false return from action.execute()

In watcher/applier/workflow_engine/default.py, we are checking the
return value of action.execute(). As the "TODO" above indicates it
(line 118), we should get rid of this and only flag an action as
failed if an exception was raised during its execute(). We will
need to update the related unit tests.

Closes-Bug: #1548383

commit_message:
OpenStack wide Error Codes for Log Messages

Error codes in Log messages provide operators a way to quickly
garner information from logs. They provide consistency across
projects and services, consistency in translations, and
consistency across the multiple log files that are spread across
both physical and virtual boundaries in Cloud based installations.

This document provides consistency across projects while
maintaining flexibility per project.

commit_message:
Change node' ip obtaining when https is forced

We need to add a workaround for an obtaining
ip address for node if the master node uses
https by default. Otherwise we couldn't fetch
it via fuel client because it doesn't
support https proto.

Closes bug: 1558527

Change-Id: I70ee6fe0fc3deea3dcaad8b60cdb409de6f1be61

Add support for ZFS (on Linux) filesystem.

Following features are supported:
- Create/delete share
- Create/delete snapshot
- Create share from snapshot
- Extend/shrink share
